			</span></a><div class="container-fluid"><header class="project-header"><div class="row"><div class="col-sm-6"><h1><font>SOV10</font></h1></div><div class="col-sm-6 info-table"><ul><li class="title"><font>Category</font></li><li class="name"><a href="http://logg.no/prosjekter/kontor"><font>office</font></a></li><li class="title  "><font>TYPE</font></li><li class="name  "><font>Commercial</font></li><li class="title  "><font>LOCATION</font></li><li class="name  "><font>Sven Oftedal way 10</font></li><li class="title item-hidden-tablet "><font>SIZE</font></li><li class="name item-hidden-tablet "><font>36 000 square meters</font></li><li class="title item-hidden-tablet "><font>STATUS</font></li><li class="name item-hidden-tablet "><font>Under construction</font></li><li class="title item-hidden-tablet item-hidden-desktop"><font>Developer</font></li><li class="name item-hidden-tablet item-hidden-desktop"><font>Aspelin Ramm Eiendom</font></li><li class="title item-hidden-tablet item-hidden-desktop"><font>INTERIOR</font></li><li class="name item-hidden-tablet item-hidden-desktop"><font>Log </font></li><li class="title item-hidden-tablet item-hidden-desktop"><font>PHOTO</font></li><li class="name item-hidden-tablet item-hidden-desktop"><font>Find Stale Felberg</font></li><li class="open-info-table"><span class="more"><span class="hide-on-phone"><span class="icon-plus"></span><font>more</font></span><font> info</font></span><span class="less"><span class="hide-on-phone"><font>less</font></span><font> info</font></span></li></ul></div></div><a href="http://logg.no/prosjekter" class="all-projects-link"><span class="size"><!--?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?--><!-- Generated by IcoMoon.io --><svg version="1.1" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" width="36" height="32" viewBox="0 0 36 32"><g></g><path d="M18.096 0l-18.096 10.448v21.552h36.19v-21.552l-18.094-10.448zM32.99 28.8h-29.79v-16.504l14.896-8.6 14.896 8.6v16.504z" fill="#000000"></path></svg></span><font>All Projects</font></a></header><div class="banner"><a class="image gallery-item" href="./projectText_files/SVEN-OV-BANNER-140312FSF038.jpg"><img alt="SOV10 FASADE" src="./projectText_files/SVEN-OV-BANNER-140312FSF038.jpg"></a></div><section class="row blocks"><div class="col-sm-6 col-md-3 block"><h2 class="block-title"><font> Background</font></h2><p><font>Aspelin Ramm Property rehabilitate buildings in Svein Oftedal way 10 for new tenants. </font><font>Central to the rehabilitation standing desire to improve energy efficiency was very poor due. </font><font>inefficient areas, thermal bridges and outdated technical equipment. </font><font>This gave great environmental savings and means that Sven Oftedal way 10 now achieves energy class B. The means to achieve these measures made in facades and roofs, demolition of inefficient building volume in the south and new technical facilities. </font><font>Buildings as described is replaced with a new building volume that follows the building's main form. </font><font>Within existing volume also established new covers approximately </font><font>4.000 m2 BTA to increase flexibility.&nbsp;</font></p></div><div class="col-sm-6 col-md-3 block"><p><font>Rehabilitation involves simultaneously that makes important aesthetic techniques in an area where there is a need for major upgrades. </font><font>The building was planned as a pure logistics buildings for businesses within warehouse and office.</font></p><p><font>Buildings listed in 1973. In 1991 the building was extended Automate warehouse and departed department. </font><font>Building has until 2011 been used by NMD. </font><font>The buildings are thought completely rebuilt and rehabilitated, inside and out for new tenants. </font><font>Service building is demolished and replaced by a new warehouse. </font><font>In existing high inventory established 2 new covers, each of 2,000 m2 gross. </font><font>When establishing parking plan 0 in automating stock achieves a reduction of paved areas on the plot. </font><font>For exterior parking established areas with grass reinforcement.</font></p></div><div class="col-sm-6 block"><a class="image gallery-item " href="./projectText_files/SVEN-OV-140312FSF017.jpg"><img alt="SOV10 OVERHUNG BOX" src="./projectText_files/SVEN-OV-140312FSF017.jpg"></a><p></p></div><div class="col-sm-12 block"><a class="image gallery-item " href="./projectText_files/SVEN-OV-130227FSF023.jpg"><img alt="SLEEP 10 - EPOXY FLOOR IN COLUMN HALL" src="./projectText_files/SVEN-OV-130227FSF023.jpg"></a><p></p></div><div class="col-sm-6 block"><a class="image gallery-item " href="./projectText_files/SVEN-OV-Untitled_Panorama1.jpg"><img alt="SOV10 - OVERVIEW IMAGE" src="./projectText_files/SVEN-OV-Untitled_Panorama1.jpg"></a><p></p></div><div class="col-sm-6 block"><a class="image gallery-item " href="./projectText_files/SVEN-OV-120912FSF320.jpg"><img alt="SOV10-RETAIL FIGURES IN STOP" src="./projectText_files/SVEN-OV-120912FSF320.jpg"></a><p></p></div><div class="col-sm-6 col-md-3 block"><h2 class="block-title"><font> Description</font></h2><p><font>All existing facades rehabilitated to reduce thermal bridges safeguard shading and aesthetics. </font><font>The existing building has cantilevered betonggesimser and balconies that create large thermal bridges. </font><font>Weighed down on this is corten steel profiles acting as shading. </font><font>The system is outdated and worked poorly. </font><font>Cantilevered building elements that create thermal bridges are cut entirely off. </font><font>New shading established as external blinds integrated in the facade systems in new climate wall. </font><font>The planned measure provides limited changes in volume, but streamlines the existing areas and transforming built exterior with more attractive facades and outdoor spaces. </font><font>Building houses now tenant who Leroy, IKEA, DHL FoodTech and Customs. </font><font>MCA.</font></p></div><div class="col-sm-6 col-md-3 block"><h2 class="block-title"><font> Materials</font></h2><p><font>It used three main materials in facades. </font><font>Glass fiber concrete and Fiber Line Composite facade plank. </font><font>Fiber Line is a transparent facade panel. </font><font>This will be used on the major stock volumes and existing technical rooms on roofs. </font><font>This provides an interesting contrast to fiber concrete used in the office building. </font><font>Fiber Line facade is illustrated in part from the back of the plate and provide outdoor areas ADDITIONAL qualities.</font></p></div><div class="col-sm-6 col-md-3 block"><p><br><font>Fibre-reinforced concrete is used primarily on kontorbygegt 05.03 floor to create a contrast to the fiber line. </font><font>Fiber Concrete Used on frames around docks to clearly identify the goods receipt. </font><font>Glass facade safeguards daylight into work zones in stores and office space in the tower block. </font><font>The new glass fa√ßade is in new climate wall in front of existing columns so that the glass facade is perceived as a continuous horizontal ribbon windows. </font><font>On facade east, which is the most exposed facade, established new main entrance and an outside "meeting room box". </font><font>Cantilevered kksisterende concrete structures retained covering in meeting the box and get glass facade from floor to ceiling and gables clad with fiber line.</font></p></div><div class="col-sm-4 col-md-3 block"><div class="materials"><div class="mask-1" style="background-image: url(http://s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/logg-web-assets/materials/GLASSFIBER_LITEN.jpg?mtime=20140613094416)"></div><div class="mask-2" style="background-image: url(http://s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/logg-web-assets/materials/GLASS-REFLEKTIVT.jpg?mtime=20140613094414)"></div><div class="mask-3" style="background-image: url(http://s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/logg-web-assets/materials/BETONG.jpg?mtime=20140613094349)"></div></div></div><div class="col-sm-6 block"><a class="image gallery-item " href="./projectText_files/SVEN-OV-bilde.jpg"><img alt="SOV 10 FASADE DETAIL" src="./projectText_files/SVEN-OV-bilde.jpg"></a><p></p></div><div class="col-sm-6 block"><a class="image gallery-item " href="./projectText_files/SVEN-OV-INTERIR.jpg"><img alt="SLEEP 10 - IKEA for occupation" src="./projectText_files/SVEN-OV-INTERIR.jpg"></a><p></p></div><div class="col-sm-12 col-md-6 block"><h2 class="block-title"><font> Outside areas</font></h2><p><font>The outdoor areas were overgrown, also in adjacent areas to the north. </font><font>Aspelin Ramm Property has repaired areas while building mass. </font><font>Utomhus becomes established new plantings which monitors adjacent open areas, and the establishment of a skate park used by neighbors. </font><font>We reestablishes the overgrown creek east of plot and create new paths through the woods.</font></p></div><div class="col-sm-6 block"><a class="image gallery-item " href="./projectText_files/SVEN-OV-140312FSF010.jpg"><img alt="SLEEP 10 - IKEA" src="./projectText_files/SVEN-OV-140312FSF010.jpg"></a><p></p></div><div class="col-sm-12 block"><a class="image gallery-item " href="./projectText_files/SVEN_OFTEDALSVEI_tverrsnitt.jpg"><img alt="SVEN OFTEDAL ROUTE sectional" src="./projectText_files/SVEN_OFTEDALSVEI_tverrsnitt.jpg"></a><p></p></div><div class="col-sm-12 block"><a class="image gallery-item " href="./projectText_files/SVEN-OFTEDALSVEI-fasade.jpg"><img alt="SVEN-OFTEDAL ROUTE fa√ßade" src="./projectText_files/SVEN-OFTEDALSVEI-fasade.jpg"></a><p></p></div><div class="col-sm-12 block"><a class="image gallery-item " href="./projectText_files/SVEN-OFTEDALSVEI-langsnitt.jpg"><img alt="SVEN-OFTEDAL ROUTE-long incision" src="./projectText_files/SVEN-OFTEDALSVEI-langsnitt.jpg"></a><p></p></div></section><section class="row share-row"><div class="col-sm-6 col-md-4"><h4><font>Share this project:</font></h4><div class="share"><a href="https://www.facebook.com/sharer/sharer.php?u=http://logg.